1
00:00:01,140 --> 00:00:04,920
Good day, dear subscribers and viewers of my channel.

2
00:00:05,720 --> 00:00:14,860
For the last while approximately the same question has been coming to me at email or via Skype from various people.

3
00:00:15,280 --> 00:00:23,440
The essence of which reduces to needing a scheme with certain protections for work with a Tesla transformer.

4
00:00:23,940 --> 00:00:28,580
Desirable that it'd be as simple as possible in making.

5
00:00:28,580 --> 00:00:45,700
Motivation different — from no experience in radio engineering, to no finances for acquiring radio-electronic components and various devices.

6
00:00:46,700 --> 00:00:50,260
Here before you now is this scheme.

7
00:00:50,340 --> 00:00:51,840
It can't be simpler.

8
00:00:52,300 --> 00:01:00,480
The scheme is assembled on one transistor and a few component details.

9
00:01:00,620 --> 00:01:12,940
Also this scheme additionally has protection between the collector and emitter of the transistor.

10
00:01:12,940 --> 00:01:14,460
This is a neon.

11
00:01:16,080 --> 00:01:20,540
And there's a resistor at the emitter of the transistor.

12
00:01:21,220 --> 00:01:25,620
The resistance at us is shown as 2 Ohm.

13
00:01:25,780 --> 00:01:31,140
This in my case is a 12 V, 21 W automotive lamp.

14
00:01:32,780 --> 00:01:36,900
Also I'll immediately answer the other often-asked question.

15
00:01:37,100 --> 00:01:38,980
Why don't videos come out on the channel?

16
00:01:39,100 --> 00:01:39,820
Where did they disappear?

17
00:01:39,920 --> 00:01:40,620
All normal?

18
00:01:40,620 --> 00:01:42,180
All good.

19
00:01:43,240 --> 00:01:44,480
Didn't disappear anywhere.

20
00:01:44,580 --> 00:01:52,380
Simply because of the fact that now the construction season is on, and I'm dealing with building my personal household.

21
00:01:53,040 --> 00:01:55,260
So all the time for now goes there.

22
00:01:55,680 --> 00:01:58,800
Extra finances are absent and I have to do everything myself.

23
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:06,220
This scheme can be referred to the category of Tesla-Kacher schemes.

24
00:02:06,780 --> 00:02:14,560
And this means that in the role of the secondary high-voltage coil of the resonator acts specifically the Tesla coil.

25
00:02:14,680 --> 00:02:16,680
And the Tesla coil requires grounding.

26
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:27,440
Grounding is connected at this point — the common wire of the scheme to the transistor emitter through a limiting resistor.

27
00:02:28,860 --> 00:02:31,260
What can this scheme do?

28
00:02:31,660 --> 00:02:42,960
This scheme can replace that block I showed for controlling Tesla transformer — bridge or half-bridge with modulation.

29
00:02:43,580 --> 00:03:00,800
Modulation in this scheme can be done further with the presence of a second Tesla transformer that'll interact with the first Tesla transformer, which we can conventionally call transmitting.

30
00:03:01,160 --> 00:03:03,560
And the second Tesla transformer will be receiving.

31
00:03:03,720 --> 00:03:07,820
Actually this system isn't exactly a transmitter.

32
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:20,760
It creates a disturbance in the environment around itself, which further in the zone of this disturbance gets into the receiver and starts their interaction with each other.

33
00:03:20,760 --> 00:03:35,240
Such a simple scheme can replace a whole box of electronics and expensive lab generators for its control.

34
00:03:35,640 --> 00:03:46,440
Despite the seeming simplicity of this scheme solution, here there are many details that need to be individually picked.

35
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:53,760
If you look, near some details there are asterisks.

36
00:03:54,700 --> 00:03:59,600
This means these details require individual picking.

37
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:09,640
No one will be able to go away from this and everyone who's going to make such a system will have to master and tune this.

38
00:04:10,640 --> 00:04:23,840
The next main moment of what this scheme realizes — it'll realize the mode that Tesla described, and this is specifically a series of oscillations.

39
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:35,260
The oscillogram that should come out on the collector I cited the picture of, further we'll examine it also on the oscilloscope.

40
00:04:36,260 --> 00:04:40,020
What else can I say about the main moments?

41
00:04:40,580 --> 00:04:46,480
In our scheme we'll use specifically a flat spiral coil.

42
00:04:46,940 --> 00:04:54,400
Such a coil is optimal for schemes on spark gaps and schemes with a series of oscillations.

43
00:04:55,100 --> 00:05:00,120
Most justifiably it showed itself in this scheme.

44
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:09,520
Here I wrote a warning that you can take the oscillogram only with grounding connected.

45
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:18,120
Mandatorily fulfill this, otherwise, if someone forgets about this, they may lose the oscilloscope.

46
00:05:19,100 --> 00:05:25,360
This scheme can also be used without grounding, then a Kacher scheme will come out.

47
00:05:26,460 --> 00:05:42,480
And to such a scheme I don't recommend connecting an oscilloscope under any conditions because any detail in this scheme without grounding connected will be under high potential.

48
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:50,320
The transistor here I use proven, which showed itself well — 2SC5200.

49
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:56,800
The collector-emitter voltage at it is 230 V limit.

50
00:05:57,280 --> 00:06:02,240
And the voltage limit at the base relative to the emitter is 5 V.

51
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:05,560
These two parameters we'll need to track.

52
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:21,780
In the scheme I also added counter-connected zeners called to protect the base of the bipolar transistor from exceeding the rating of 5 V so the base-emitter junction wasn't broken.

53
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:33,120
Also this neon I introduced — here you see also an asterisk stands — and the resistance, connected in series to it, is also marked with an asterisk.

54
00:06:33,120 --> 00:06:36,900
These two details will need to be picked.

55
00:06:36,960 --> 00:06:47,420
They're picked based on the calculation that the neon started its glow at voltage from 100 to 150 V.

56
00:06:48,180 --> 00:06:56,300
This 3 kOhm resistance is a current-limiting resistance so the neon didn't fail further.

57
00:06:57,070 --> 00:07:16,440
In this scheme an ancient method of protection is applied, which was known to radio amateurs who worked on schemes with radio tubes — when the cathode of the tube is raised relative to the common wire through a resistor.

58
00:07:16,440 --> 00:07:19,400
And connected capacitors are in parallel.

59
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:32,580
This solution serves as additional transistor protection from potential rise relative to the minus of the scheme.

60
00:07:32,580 --> 00:07:53,180
When modulation will be done further on interaction with the receiving Tesla transformer, there'll be a moment that the common point will jump relative to minus and this can fail the transistor.

61
00:07:53,180 --> 00:08:03,520
These jumps the 100 µF electrolytic capacitor will smooth, this way it'll protect the transistor.

62
00:08:04,900 --> 00:08:11,480
Now we can move to the inductor and high-voltage coil.

63
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:13,180
How are they built?

64
00:08:14,300 --> 00:08:23,620
These are discrete systems, consequently, all of us are subjected to the length rule in this scheme.

65
00:08:24,420 --> 00:08:34,740
That is, we can go by structure — take the inductor as a basis, or we take as a basis the turn length of the high-voltage coil.

66
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:51,580
If we take as a basis the high-voltage coil and its turn length — as I usually do — then I multiply the turn length of the high-voltage coil by a whole number and get the inductor length.

67
00:08:51,580 --> 00:09:05,800
Pay attention that in this scheme the high-voltage coil is wound to the right — that is, if you look at the pipe from above, the wire winds clockwise and goes to the grounding side.

68
00:09:06,280 --> 00:09:14,140
Right-side winding clockwise, and also the flat coil at us is wound — right-side winding.

69
00:09:14,140 --> 00:09:30,480
Plus is connected to the power source at the central point most close to the high-voltage coil, and the collector is connected to the start of the winding.

70
00:09:31,380 --> 00:09:36,900
It's marked with number 2 — two stands near the collector of the transistor.

71
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:54,700
For power, the scheme when you conduct experiments — I recommend from a battery, and possibly you'll need a converter from 12 V, and should convert from 3 to 100 V.

72
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:59,320
This scheme with these ratings at me launches at voltage of 3 V.

73
00:10:00,320 --> 00:10:25,100
Here in such a system, if you tune the correct operating mode, you can easily drive in 50 W of energy and at that the transistor will be in optimal operating mode, won't heat, and the whole energy will transfer from primary coil to secondary.

74
00:10:25,100 --> 00:10:32,620
By this way maximum matching between them will be achieved and the system will work optimally.

75
00:10:33,140 --> 00:10:47,700
Further we'll examine two cases when the system is not optimally tuned, what oscillograms will be, and the system in such a mode — and look at the temperature mode of transistor operation.

76
00:10:47,700 --> 00:10:53,920
Here I marked how to calculate the inductor length.

77
00:10:54,860 --> 00:11:06,480
And also here it's written that the inductor wire length is counted from the collector of the transistor directly to the plus lead on electrolytic capacitors.

78
00:11:06,480 --> 00:11:12,380
Here this electrolytic capacitor, 200 µF, 400 V.

79
00:11:12,940 --> 00:11:23,640
Parallel are placed capacitors called to remove high-frequency pickups so they didn't get on the electrolytic.

80
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:26,920
This is 0.1 µF at 630 V.

81
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:38,360
And an accumulator capacitor of 2.2 µF that accelerates the pulse front on the collector.

82
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:48,860
Since electrolytics, compared to quality film capacitors, have some charge release time.

83
00:11:49,860 --> 00:11:59,980
Also you see there's a capacitor 0.1 µF at 630 V, on the emitter relative to minus.

84
00:12:00,120 --> 00:12:09,660
This is also a capacitor responsible for damping the high-frequency pickup that'll inevitably circulate.

85
00:12:09,660 --> 00:12:18,260
Also you can see that between the high-voltage coil and the transistor base there's a current-limiting resistor at 1 Ohm.

86
00:12:19,260 --> 00:12:27,760
And here are two main details that create on the transistor base the bias necessary for its work.

87
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:31,580
These resistances will need to be picked as well.

88
00:12:31,680 --> 00:12:35,240
In my case they're 6.8 kOhm and 2.7 kOhm.

89
00:12:35,760 --> 00:12:39,040
But this is my case — they're picked under my scheme.

90
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:47,620
Also further I'll show you what dependency between these resistances and turn count in the inductor.

91
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:52,800
And how to achieve such an interesting transistor operating mode.

92
00:12:53,120 --> 00:12:55,600
So, the scheme made in iron.

93
00:12:56,180 --> 00:13:03,300
This is an accumulator capacity from two 200 µF 400 V capacitors.

94
00:13:03,300 --> 00:13:09,840
Then goes a film capacitor 2.2 µF at 630 V.

95
00:13:10,360 --> 00:13:18,980
This capacitor 0.1 µF 630 V for damping HF pickups passing through it.

96
00:13:19,520 --> 00:13:25,420
Pay attention that I brought out legs to which the resistors are soldered.

97
00:13:26,460 --> 00:13:33,660
This is done so I could conveniently pick details without disassembling the whole common scheme.

98
00:13:33,780 --> 00:13:35,560
On the heat sink the transistor is located.

99
00:13:36,260 --> 00:13:46,660
The heat sink is made with reserve so I could show you the operating mode when the transistor will strongly heat — what losses will go.

100
00:13:47,060 --> 00:13:54,320
And then we can look by temperature when the transistor will be slightly above room temperature.

101
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:59,000
And this system will work in order on 50 W.

102
00:14:00,520 --> 00:14:03,880
The inductor wires are connected at these points.

103
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:08,300
This is accordingly the lamp at 2 Ohm.

104
00:14:09,460 --> 00:14:13,600
All resistances here are 1 W — I also marked it on the scheme.

105
00:14:13,960 --> 00:14:18,920
Less here is not worth putting, otherwise they'll strongly heat and may burn.

106
00:14:19,920 --> 00:14:26,820
The coil I used here is high-voltage.

107
00:14:27,380 --> 00:14:35,760
It's made with a thick conductor, wire cross-section 0.96 mm.

108
00:14:38,180 --> 00:14:44,920
That is, not every scheme can qualitatively swing such a coil.

109
00:14:44,920 --> 00:14:47,140
But this scheme allows.

110
00:14:47,420 --> 00:14:52,660
This high-voltage coil has a work calculation at exactly 1 MHz.

111
00:14:53,780 --> 00:14:59,860
We know that the wavelength for 1 MHz is 300 meters.

112
00:15:00,060 --> 00:15:03,040
Consequently a quarter should be 75.

113
00:15:03,220 --> 00:15:09,740
But at more accurate count here it turns out 74.5 m.

114
00:15:09,740 --> 00:15:15,660
If you enter the wave propagation speed more accurately in the calculation formula.

115
00:15:16,060 --> 00:15:20,400
How to calculate a Tesla transformer look on my channel in previous videos.

116
00:15:20,700 --> 00:15:25,180
There are detailed descriptions of how to do this.

117
00:15:26,740 --> 00:15:33,700
Now let's also examine the principle of how to bring this coil to the needed frequency for us.

118
00:15:34,980 --> 00:15:40,900
Pay attention that the coil now has no additional capacity.

119
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:43,640
Here is the hot end.

120
00:15:44,760 --> 00:15:55,920
The hot end is the end of the conductor of the high-voltage coil at which the maximum voltage potential is.

121
00:15:56,420 --> 00:16:00,840
At the cold end at this moment we have the maximum current.

122
00:16:00,840 --> 00:16:02,400
There's an interesting moment.

123
00:16:02,980 --> 00:16:15,200
Professional electronics, radio amateurs often protest against the fact that these scheme solutions are separated into a separate group called Kachers.

124
00:16:17,080 --> 00:16:23,580
They say, why did you invent a name for this scheme when this is a usual self-generator on one transistor.

125
00:16:24,440 --> 00:16:26,180
And what's interesting here.

126
00:16:26,180 --> 00:16:31,340
Why are these schemes brought into a separate category of Kachers?

127
00:16:31,520 --> 00:16:35,560
Because in this scheme first, Kirchhoff's law is violated.

128
00:16:35,960 --> 00:16:48,760
This is expressed in that if you take the common wire of the oscilloscope and connect it to minus of the power source, and stand on the collector with the probe, you'll see positive pulses on the collector.

129
00:16:48,760 --> 00:16:56,480
Also you can now stand with the common wire of the oscilloscope on plus power.

130
00:16:57,000 --> 00:17:03,620
And if you look at the pulses on the collector, then relative to plus they'll also be positive.

131
00:17:03,900 --> 00:17:07,760
At the time when on a usual self-generator the polarity will change.

132
00:17:08,570 --> 00:17:19,260
And the second not unimportant moment is that this scheme lets us hold the primary coil in resonance mode.

133
00:17:19,760 --> 00:17:22,180
That is, the inductor of the high-voltage transformer.

134
00:17:22,580 --> 00:17:24,780
How is this resonance mode achieved?

135
00:17:25,160 --> 00:17:33,540
This is the mode called when current and voltage in this conductor are shifted practically by 90 degrees.

136
00:17:33,540 --> 00:17:35,820
Striving for this shift.

137
00:17:36,660 --> 00:17:47,980
And automatically it turns out that this — effectively a piece of wire of a couple meters — is in resonance mode without picking parallel capacity for it.

138
00:17:48,800 --> 00:17:52,860
When the current doesn't correspond to the voltage pulse.

139
00:17:52,960 --> 00:17:54,560
They're spaced in time.

140
00:17:54,560 --> 00:18:03,240
These are two main features by which these scheme solutions are separated into a separate category of Kachers.

141
00:18:04,020 --> 00:18:08,060
So, the first moment when the whole system is assembled, connected.

142
00:18:08,820 --> 00:18:12,140
Observed the rule of winding in one and the same direction.

143
00:18:12,840 --> 00:18:17,420
Connect to minus of the scheme the grounding wire — here is the conductor.

144
00:18:18,180 --> 00:18:22,480
Connect the common of the oscilloscope probe to the same point.

145
00:18:22,480 --> 00:18:25,180
And connect grounding.

146
00:18:25,460 --> 00:18:28,960
And here this black terminal — this is also minus.

147
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:31,500
Also connect plus.

148
00:18:31,920 --> 00:18:37,760
And apply to the scheme the minimum voltage at which it can launch.

149
00:18:37,920 --> 00:18:41,600
Here in my case the probe, pay attention, hangs in air.

150
00:18:42,260 --> 00:18:47,480
The system launched and its launch starts from 7 V.

151
00:18:48,040 --> 00:18:50,240
This is consumption of 6 hundredths of an amp.

152
00:18:50,920 --> 00:18:57,860
How can you determine that the coil is not in the optimal operating mode?

153
00:18:58,600 --> 00:19:00,900
This is determined by our calculation.

154
00:19:00,980 --> 00:19:05,280
We know that here 74.5 m of conductor in this coil.

155
00:19:05,860 --> 00:19:09,520
Means it should work at frequency 1 MHz.

156
00:19:09,700 --> 00:19:12,820
74.5 m for MHz this is quarter.

157
00:19:13,900 --> 00:19:17,000
So now I'll bring my hand.

158
00:19:17,820 --> 00:19:27,680
And if the coil actually wants to switch to a lower operating frequency, then the amplitude in the system will rise.

159
00:19:27,820 --> 00:19:31,540
My hand will be an isolated capacity relative to earth.

160
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:36,860
Will lower frequency and see an increase of oscillation amplitude.

161
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:40,000
At that the consumption shouldn't increase.

162
00:19:40,380 --> 00:19:43,780
So I'll bring my hand and we'll observe the oscillogram.

163
00:19:45,100 --> 00:19:48,940
Visible that the amplitude now.

164
00:19:49,380 --> 00:19:51,880
And in the upper corner — this is frequency.

165
00:19:51,980 --> 00:19:55,660
For now don't pay attention to it, the oscilloscope doesn't capture it.

166
00:19:55,840 --> 00:19:56,600
Bring hand.

167
00:19:57,580 --> 00:20:02,200
You see the amplitude clearly increases.

168
00:20:02,760 --> 00:20:04,660
Hand closer, amplitude up.

169
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:08,760
Means yes, actually the coil lacks additional capacity.

170
00:20:09,720 --> 00:20:11,260
Also consumption.

171
00:20:11,480 --> 00:20:12,660
Here it doesn't change.

172
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:15,200
Bring, remove.

173
00:20:16,020 --> 00:20:17,160
All in place.

174
00:20:18,060 --> 00:20:25,600
Now I can add supply voltage and determine accurate frequency.

175
00:20:25,740 --> 00:20:27,160
Here the oscilloscope captures.

176
00:20:27,840 --> 00:20:30,840
Entered into frequency capture normally.

177
00:20:31,220 --> 00:20:34,980
And see that it's practically 1.6 MHz.

178
00:20:35,980 --> 00:20:36,960
Bring hand.

179
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:40,820
Here also in this mode amplitude increases.

180
00:20:41,080 --> 00:20:43,520
And now we can track frequency.

181
00:20:45,020 --> 00:20:50,320
From 1.58 it reduces.

182
00:20:50,800 --> 00:20:51,740
So, 1.3.

183
00:20:53,440 --> 00:20:58,840
Means, I conclude that this coil needs isolated capacity.

184
00:20:59,260 --> 00:21:10,380
If at bringing the hand to the coil the amplitude on the contrary fell, then in this case it'd be clear that on the contrary the capacity at the coil needs to be reduced.

185
00:21:10,660 --> 00:21:14,500
That is, this is a coil already made geometrically incorrectly.

186
00:21:14,640 --> 00:21:21,480
Here you'd have to unwind wire because there's already interturn capacity at us.

187
00:21:22,360 --> 00:21:34,120
And to reduce it you can't, except either stretch the turns of the high-voltage coil, make a gap between them, or unwind physical meters of conductor.

188
00:21:35,100 --> 00:21:42,740
In the same mode, all as you've seen many times — neon lamps will glow here near the hot end.

189
00:21:43,320 --> 00:21:46,160
Near the cold ones they shouldn't glow.

190
00:21:46,320 --> 00:21:49,280
Pass, burns, here no.

191
00:21:49,440 --> 00:21:57,060
Also you can pass with the oscilloscope probe — here will be maximum amplitude.

192
00:21:57,060 --> 00:22:00,080
And here will be amplitude at zero.

193
00:22:01,700 --> 00:22:05,120
Now we switch to picking isolated capacity.

194
00:22:05,220 --> 00:22:09,580
I picked it in advance, and now I'll show some stages.

195
00:22:10,340 --> 00:22:14,100
As isolated capacity I'll apply such a system.

196
00:22:14,260 --> 00:22:18,340
Here I'll solder the hot end of the high-voltage coil.

197
00:22:18,960 --> 00:22:21,560
Inside is a ball from Christmas tree toys.

198
00:22:22,100 --> 00:22:25,640
How to make such isolated capacity I showed earlier on the channel.

199
00:22:25,640 --> 00:22:28,120
The isolated capacity is installed.

200
00:22:28,760 --> 00:22:30,600
I apply power to the system.

201
00:22:37,190 --> 00:22:42,250
Approximately 6 hundredths amp, 7 V.

202
00:22:42,730 --> 00:22:48,470
Immediately you can pay attention that with the isolated capacity the frequency became lower,

203
00:22:52,210 --> 00:22:54,250
1170 kHz.

204
00:22:55,970 --> 00:22:59,370
And the field around the coil increased.

205
00:22:59,650 --> 00:23:02,270
That is, now we can see our neon.

206
00:23:03,290 --> 00:23:09,510
It lights up already at a more distant distance from the coil.

207
00:23:09,670 --> 00:23:13,190
At that the consumption at us is the same.

208
00:23:13,390 --> 00:23:18,090
And we can observe such a moment that the system launch became more stable.

209
00:23:18,330 --> 00:23:22,610
And we can launch it already starting from 3 V.

210
00:23:24,230 --> 00:23:27,830
4 V and it calmly launched.

211
00:23:29,410 --> 00:23:31,050
You see the frequency already.

212
00:23:32,230 --> 00:23:34,230
I'll try to make it less.

213
00:23:36,970 --> 00:23:38,250
3 V.

214
00:23:40,190 --> 00:23:41,690
The system works.

215
00:23:45,570 --> 00:23:55,630
Now we determine that we can accurately examine our frequency.

216
00:23:57,470 --> 00:24:01,090
You see that we didn't reach the calculated frequency.

217
00:24:01,230 --> 00:24:04,810
Consequently, we still need to increase isolated capacity.

218
00:24:06,010 --> 00:24:10,690
Since I picked all the details in advance, this won't pose difficulty.

219
00:24:10,690 --> 00:24:17,870
Now we'll install such a nimbus on our coil.

220
00:24:18,490 --> 00:24:25,050
A head of some Saint Patrick will come out.

221
00:24:27,090 --> 00:24:30,250
Such a bald one with a nimbus.

222
00:24:32,370 --> 00:24:34,550
Such a funny coil came out.

